      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are fork-tender, drain them in a colander and shake them until they're fluffy</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>remaining rosemary</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant – this is your<strong> rosemary oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1696950271985-x200.jpg",
