    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once melted, add 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span><strong> </strong><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 30 secs, stirring to form a paste</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and stir in your <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong> and<strong> Marmite</strong></p><p>Gradually add the <strong>stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 10-12 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>gravy</strong></p>",
